  "texts": [
    "Observations about biased SK modelAs presented in Corollary 6.1, there is a deep connection between arbitrarily-weighted MaxCut and the SK model.",
    "The SK model is given in Equation (70) and has couplings J uv ∼ N (0, 1).",
    "A natural generalization to consider is a model which has couplings J uv ∼ N (µ, σ 2) with arbitrary µ and σ.",
    "More generally, we can allow for the bias to be a function of the number of spins, i.e.",
    "When µ(N) ̸ = 0, we call this the biased SK model, and when µ(N) = 0, we call it the standard SK model."
